<div class="rules-container">
    <div class="rules-header">Muslim Way of Burial</div>

    <div class="rules-section">
        <h3>Introduction</h3>
        <p>In Islam, burial is a sacred and simple process emphasizing dignity, modesty, and return to Allah. It must be done as soon as possible after death following Islamic guidelines based on Quran and Sunnah.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="rules-section">
        <h3>Step-by-Step Islamic Burial Procedure</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <strong>Confirm Death:</strong> When a Muslim dies, say <em>“Inna Lillahi wa inna ilayhi raji’un”</em> and inform family and the local Islamic center.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Ghusl (Ritual Washing):</strong> Wash the deceased (same gender preferred; spouse allowed). Use clean water and soap, followed by three full washes (or more if needed, odd number), ending with camphor (kāfūr).
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Kafan (Shrouding):</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Men: 3 white cotton sheets</li>
                    <li>Women: 5 pieces (including chest wrap and head cover)</li>
                </ul>
                Wrap the body tightly and modestly.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Salat al-Janazah (Funeral Prayer):</strong> Offer the Janazah prayer at the masjid, cemetery, or open area (see Janazah Prayer page).
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Burial (Dafn):</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>The grave should be perpendicular to the Qiblah.</li>
                    <li>The body is placed on the right side, facing Qiblah.</li>
                    <li>Use phrases like: <em>“Bismillahi wa ‘ala millati Rasoolillah”</em>.</li>
                    <li>Men should lower male bodies; female bodies are ideally lowered by close female relatives.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Filling the Grave:</strong> After burial, cover the grave with soil completely, forming a small mound. Everyone may participate.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Supplication at the Grave:</strong> After burial, make du‘a for the deceased. Common supplication:
                <blockquote>
                    “O Allah, forgive him/her and grant them ease and peace in the grave, and make their final abode Jannah.”
                </blockquote>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="rules-section">
        <h3>Important Reminders</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Do not delay the burial unnecessarily.</li>
            <li>No extravagant coffins or tombs – simplicity is Sunnah.</li>
            <li>Women may attend burial from a distance (according to many scholars).</li>
            <li>No wailing, loud crying, or un-Islamic customs.</li>
            <li>Recite Qur'an privately but not as a ritual requirement at the grave.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="note-box">
        <strong>Note:</strong> The Prophet ﷺ said, <em>"Break not the bones of your dead, for it is painful to them as it is to the living."</em> — So treat the deceased with the utmost respect and care.
    </div>
</div>
